    "title": "Oracle decimal scaling is ignored, so non-18-decimal feeds misprice collateral by orders of magnitude",
    "locations": [
      "src/interfaces/IOracle.sol:5",
      "src/protocol/pair/ResupplyPairCore.sol:573",
      "src/protocol/ResupplyPair.sol:176"
    ],
    "claim": "The pair hardcodes the exchange-rate conversion as `1e36 / price` and never normalizes by `IOracle.decimals()` or validates the replacement oracle's scale, so any feed that does not return 18-decimal prices skews all LTV and liquidation math by a power-of-ten factor.",
    "impact": "A mis-scaled oracle can make healthy positions look insolvent, freeze withdrawals/liquidations, or undervalue debt enough to let borrowers extract far more stablecoins than their collateral should support.",
    "paths": [
      "A pair is deployed or updated with an oracle whose `decimals()` is not 18.",
      "Any call to `_updateExchangeRate()` computes an incorrect `exchangeRate`.",
      "Borrow, liquidation, redemption, and collateral-removal flows use the distorted price in solvency and collateral-accounting checks."
    ]
  },
